==English==

===Adjective===
'''stale'''
# Having lost its [[freshness]] from age. Stale food, for instance, is food which is still edible but has lost its deliciousness.
#:''The steak is as '''stale''' as the beer.''
#:''If you don't enter a room for some days, the air will become '''stale'''.''
# No longer [[new]]; no longer [[interesting]]; old; as, stale news, a stale joke, etc.

===Noun===
'''stale'''
# (Shakespearian) A woman who is "no longer fresh" or who has lost her virginity, as in Shakespeare's ''Much Ado About Nothing''
#: ''"I stand dishonor'd, that have gone about/To link my dear friend to a common stale" (Act IV, Scene i, lines 59-60)''

